      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8;">

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
          The Uintah Basin is one of the best hunting regions in Utah — elk, mule deer, pronghorn, waterfowl, and upland birds all within a short drive of Vernal. That means a lot of gear: rifles, bows, tree stands, game carts, decoys, camping equipment, coolers, ATVs, and trailers. If your garage is already full, you need a place to keep it all secure and protected between seasons.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">Why Hunters Choose Fort Knox</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Mouse-proof containers.</strong> This is the biggest deal for hunters. Mice chew through fabric, leather, nylon straps, wiring, and soft cases. In a standard wood-frame storage unit, rodent damage to hunting gear is almost guaranteed if you're storing it off-season. Fort Knox's all-steel containers are completely sealed — no gaps, no entry points, no mice. Your camo, packs, optics, and tree stands come out exactly as you put them in.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>24/7 access.</strong> Hunting season doesn't follow a 9-to-5 schedule. You can load your trailer and grab your gear at 3 AM before an early-morning hunt. No waiting for office hours or gate codes that only work during the day.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Wide driveways for trailers and ATVs.</strong> Fort Knox has extra-wide graveled driveways designed for semi-trucks — so your truck-and-trailer rig, ATV trailer, or side-by-side fits through easily.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--primary-dark); margin: 30px 0 15px;">What Fits in a Fort Knox Container?</h2>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">A 20ft container holds a full ATV, camp gear, multiple gun cases, tree stands, decoys, and coolers. A 40ft container can store all of that plus a side-by-side, additional ATVs, a full camp kitchen setup, and seasonal clothing and equipment for multiple family members.</p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">If you also need to park an ATV trailer, boat, or camper, Fort Knox offers outdoor parking spaces for $100/month.</p>

        
